			<ns0:name>g...@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/101919841667397351009/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">If they are not requesting an alpha channel the command buffer should be enforcing no alpha channel even if the GPU gives an alpha channel. If it's not it sounds like there's a bug.

On the other hand, I'm not sure that code makes any sense for anything other than real backbuffers. Everything else renders to textures through fbos so we control the format 100%



